We recommended that Management require the BAC, with the assistance of the TWG and BAC Secretariat, to:
Post the Invitation to Bid,  Contract and NTP in the LGU website;
Ensure that pre-procurement conference is conducted for procurement of goods costing ₱2,000,000.00 and above;
Require all bidders to support the submitted SLCC with Contract, Certificate of Completion and Certificate of Acceptance;
Require the bidders to use the prescribed forms in the bidding documents and emphasize the possibility of non-acceptance of bid for non-compliance;
Ensure that the NTP was issued to the winning biddings within seven calendar days from the date of approval of the contract;
Conduct the mandatory review and evaluation of the terms, conditions, and specifications in the bidding documents, in case there was a failure of bidding; and
Indicate their initial in every page of the original copies of the bid received and opened.
